content: Bootstrap 3 allows you to make the images responsive by adding a class ..img-responsive to the <.img> tag.
..img-responsive class applies max-width: 100%; and height: auto; to the image so that it scales nicely to the parent element.
It specifies static for a backdrop, if you don't want the modal to be closed when the user clicks outside of the modal.
It closes the modal when escape key is pressed; set to false to disable.
It shows the modal when initialized.
Using the jQuery .load method, injects content into the modal body. If an href with a valid URL is added, it will load that content.
